And then lift them
up and eat them.

24:50.364 --> 24:53.451
♪

24:56.162 --> 24:57.788
Oh, very refined.

24:59.248 --> 25:01.166
You know some of these
dishes, the character,

25:01.167 --> 25:03.543
is very similar to what
you get on the street,

25:03.585 --> 25:05.212
but it's just done
so beautifully.

25:05.254 --> 25:06.922
Well, we were talking
the other day

25:06.964 --> 25:08.984
- that so many of the dishes
- we were eating in the restaurant

25:09.008 --> 25:11.551
Started out... these were
not invented by chefs

25:11.593 --> 25:14.013
or even cooks, they were
invented by farmers

25:14.054 --> 25:15.931
uh, and hungry people.

25:15.932 --> 25:18.893
I mean, and that's certainly
the story of... of much

25:18.894 --> 25:19.935
of French cooking.

25:19.977 --> 25:21.561
I mean, correct me if I'm wrong.

25:21.603 --> 25:22.729
For sure.

25:22.730 --> 25:25.732
But when... when you can
achieve refinement

25:25.774 --> 25:29.153
and you keep the soul
food in the process

25:29.195 --> 25:31.155
you don't have only pretty food,

25:31.197 --> 25:33.573
you have amazing food.

25:33.615 --> 25:35.409
♪

